CI/CD Conventions

When editing pipelines, infrastructure automation, or deployment workflows, follow modern CI/CD and DevOps best practices. Consider the cicd-expert skill for GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform, and release strategies. Use /cicd or @cicd in Agent chat for full skill behavior.

Use trunk-based development or well-defined Git flow.

All PRs must run automated tests, linting, and security checks.

Enforce formatting (black, isort, flake8/ruff) before merge.

Build Docker images with multi-stage builds.

Tag images using immutable versioning (commit SHA or semantic version).

Avoid secrets in pipelines — use secure secret managers.

Use environment promotion strategy (dev → staging → prod).

Prefer infrastructure-as-code (Terraform) over manual changes.

Include rollback strategy in deployment design.
